    <string name="tips_title">Super Auto Ito</string>
    <string name="section_game">The Game</string>
    <string name="game_desc_1">Assemble the most powerful team of kyara from the Junji Ito universe and let them fight in auto-battles.</string>
    <string name="game_desc_2">Each match is a test of strategy: choosing who joins the team, the order in which they fight, and how to combine their unique skills.</string>
    <string name="section_cards">The Cards</string>
    <string name="cards_desc_1">Each card represents a Junji Ito character (Tomie, Souichi, among others) and has two attributes:</string>
    <string name="cards_desc_2">• Attack\n• Defense\nAttack always reduces the opponent\'s defense.</string>
    <string name="cards_desc_3">Each character also has characteristics that affect their skills:</string>
    <string name="cards_desc_4">Male, Female, Child, Corpse, Supernatural, and Common.</string>
    <string name="section_skills">Skills</string>
    <string name="skills_desc_1">Every character has a unique skill. They are divided into five types:</string>
    <string name="skills_desc_2">• Buff\n• Debuff\n• Deck change\n• Summoning\n• Specials</string>
    <string name="skills_desc_3">Each skill has an activation timing, target, and criteria based on the target\'s characteristics:</string>
    <string name="skills_desc_4">Timings: On kill, On death, Battle start.\nTargets: Self, Enemy, Friend, All, Random, Killer, Deceased.</string>
    <string name="section_deck">The Deck</string>
    <string name="deck_desc_1">At the start of the match, 8 characters are drawn:</string>
    <string name="deck_desc_2">• 6 enter the main team\n• 2 stay in reserve</string>
    <string name="deck_desc_3">You can reorganize the team order and swap characters between main and reserve freely.</string>
    <string name="deck_desc_4">Every round, it is mandatory to move at least one card from the reserve to the main team.</string>
    <string name="deck_desc_5">Upon suffering a defeat, you can buy a random character from the shop and place it in the reserve. It can then enter the main team.</string>
    <string name="section_battle">The Battle</string>
    <string name="battle_desc_1">Battles happen in two phases:</string>
    <string name="battle_desc_2">1. Start Phase: start skills are activated.\n2. Confrontation Phase: characters attack each other following the deck order.</string>
    <string name="battle_desc_3">The winner is whoever still has cards at the end of the combat.</string>
